               <p>RUTH MOLLINEUX. I am the wife of John Mollineux, we live in <placeName id="t18170917-135-crimeloc676">Hosier-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-135-crimeloc676" type="placeName" value="Hosier-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170917-135-crimeloc676" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170917-135-off674 t18170917-135-crimeloc676"></join>. On the 2d of August, the prisoner came to the private door, and asked for an errand-boy's place; he went away, and in a few minutes his companion came into the shop for a halfpenny-worth of waters; I turned round, and saw the prisoner taking the watch off the mantle-piece - He ran out, I followed him and brought him back - He had not got the watch upon him.</p>
               <p>HENRY TURNER. I am a pawnbroker. On the evening of the 2d of August the watch was pledged with me. Mollineux claimed it at the office - I do not know who pledged it.</p>
               <p>JOHN SIBLEY. I am a tailor. I saw the prisoner by the fire-place in Mrs. Mollineux's parlour, with his hands in his pocket.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
